claims:
Claims 1. A vehicle comprising: an entrance to an interior compartment of the vehicle; a step assembly located adjacent the entrance of the vehicle and comprising at least one step and at least one riser; wherein the at least one riser is attached to and substantially perpendicular to the at least one step; wherein the step assembly includes an opening that allows access behind the step assembly; wherein the opening is formed from both a portion of the at least one riser and a portion of the at least one step; wherein the at least one riser and the at least one step are configured to attract or produce a magnetic force; a lid comprising an at least one step section and an at least one riser section; wherein the lid includes a hinge that allows selective movement of the lid between open and closed positions with respect to the opening in the step assembly; wherein the lid covers the opening in the step assembly when in the closed position such that the at least one step section rests on the portion of the at least one step adjacent the opening, and the at least one riser section abuts the portion of the at least one riser adjacent the opening; wherein the at least one step section and the at least one riser section each includes a top surface and an underside surface; wherein a securement is attached to the underside surface of either or both the at least one step section and the at least one riser section; 

 wherein the securement is either a magnet which includes a magnetic force or a material that attracts a magnetic force; wherein the attraction between the at least one step and the at least one riser to the lid secures the lid to the at least one step and at least one riser; and wherein there is no securement structure extending from the top surfaces of either the step section or the riser section. 2. The vehicle of Claim 1, wherein the lid is hingedly attached to the at least one riser by the hinge. 3. The vehicle of Claim 1, wherein the at least one riser section of the lid includes first and second riser sections and the at least one step section is located between the first and second riser sections; wherein the step assembly includes a second riser wherein the step is located between the at least one riser and the second riser; wherein the step assembly includes an opening that allows access behind the step assembly; wherein the opening is formed from the portion of the at least one riser, the portion of the at least one step, and a portion of the second riser; wherein the hinge of the lid is attached to the second riser section of the lid and the portion of the second riser of the step assembly to allow selective movement of the lid between open and closed positions with respect to the opening in the step assembly; and wherein the securement is a magnet which includes a magnetic force attracted toward the at least one step and the at least one riser. 4. The vehicle of Claim 1, wherein the securement is not substantially visible above the top surface of the at least one step and riser sections. 5. The vehicle of Claim 1, wherein behind the opening is a battery compartment. 6. The vehicle of Claim 1, wherein behind the opening is a storage area housing structures selected from the group consisting of engine, transmission, generator, and storage compartment. 7. The vehicle of Claim 1, wherein the step assembly is in the form of a step- well. 8. The vehicle of Claim 1, wherein the portion of the at least one riser and the portion of the at least one step forms a periphery about the opening that includes a frame. 9. The vehicle of Claim 8, wherein the underside of the lid includes a plurality of receiver plates configured to engage at least one magnet located on the frame. 10. The vehicle of Claim 1, further comprising a seal located about a periphery of a portion of an underside of the lid and configured to block debris. 11. A vehicle comprising: an entrance to an interior compartment of the vehicle; a step assembly located adjacent the entrance of the vehicle and comprising at least one step and at least one riser; wherein the at least one riser is attached to and substantially perpendicular to the at least one step; wherein the step assembly includes an opening; wherein the opening is formed in a portion of the at least one riser; a lid comprising an at least one riser section; wherein the lid includes a hinge that allows selective movement of the lid between open and closed positions with respect to the opening in the step assembly; 

 wherein the at least one riser section of the lid covers the opening in the step assembly when in the closed position; wherein the at least one riser section includes a top surface and an underside surface; wherein a securement is located between the underside surface of the at least one riser section and the at least one riser; wherein the securement is a magnet that creates a magnetic force between the lid and the step assembly; and wherein there is no securement structure extending from the top surfaces of either the step section or the riser section. 12. The vehicle of Claim 11, wherein the lid includes at least one receiver plate and the securement is attached to the step assembly; wherein the at least one receiver plate is configured to be magnetically attracted to the securement to hold the lid over the opening of the step assembly. 13. The vehicle of Claim 11, wherein the lid includes the securement and the at least one receiver plate is attached to the step assembly; wherein the at least one receiver plate is configured to be magnetically attracted to the securement to hold the lid over the opening of the step assembly. 14. The vehicle of Claim 11, wherein the at least one receiver plate is made of galvanized steel having a sufficient attraction to the magnet when in close proximity thereto to keep the lid closed unless lifted open. 15. The vehicle of Claim 11, wherein the magnet aligns the lid over the opening. 16. The vehicle of Claim 11, wherein a compression seal is located between the lid and the step assembly. 17. A vehicle comprising: an entrance to an interior compartment of the vehicle; a step assembly located adjacent the entrance of the vehicle and comprising at least one step and at least one riser; wherein the at least one riser is attached to and substantially perpendicular to the at least one step; wherein the step assembly includes an opening; wherein the opening is formed in a portion of the at least one step; a lid comprising an at least one step section; wherein the lid includes a hinge that allows selective movement of the lid between open and closed positions with respect to the opening in the step assembly; wherein the lid covers the opening in the step assembly when in the closed position; wherein the lid includes a top surface and an underside surface; a securement is located between the underside surface of the lid and the step assembly; wherein the securement is a magnet that creates a magnetic force between the lid and the step assembly; and wherein there is no securement structure extending from the top surfaces of the lid. 18. The vehicle of Claim 17, wherein the lid includes at least one receiver plate and the securement is attached to the step assembly; wherein the at least one receiver plate is configured to be magnetically attracted to the securement to hold the lid over the opening of the step assembly. 19. The vehicle of Claim 17, wherein the lid includes the securement and the at least one receiver plate is attached to the step assembly; wherein the at least one receiver plate is configured to be magnetically attracted to the securement to hold the lid over the opening of the step assembly. 20. The vehicle of Claim 17, wherein the at least one receiver plate is made of galvanized steel having a sufficient attraction to the magnet when in close proximity thereto to keep the lid closed unless lifted open. 21. The vehicle of Claim 17, wherein the magnet aligns the lid over the opening. 22. The vehicle of Claim 17, wherein a compression seal is located between the lid and the step assembly.
